Question Statement¶

Use python to write an optimizer.

  1. Suppose we initially have a basket of $10 million CSI300 underlying stocks, with equal weights.
  2. Use Markowitz optimization to build a portfolio, maximize future return and minimize risk.
  3. For risk calculation, you can either use Barra Data (if you have), or past 5 years daily data to calculate Cov matrix.
  4. Each component weight should deviate from CSI300 weight less than 3%.
  5. Turnover rate should be less than 15%.
  6. For alpha, you can generate random number, alpha itself is not important.

Assumptions¶

  1. Investment universe: CSI 300 + cash (without forward looking / survival bias)
  2. Long only, no transaction cost
  3. Daily rebalance:
    • Step 1: Return forecast from momentum factor
    • Step 2: Risk estimation, 5-year covariance
    • Step 3: Run optimizer (input: return forecast, risk, T-1 position; with constraints)
    • Step 4: Get trades and new position
  4. Backtesting period: 2021 ~ present
  5. Implement framework: https://www.cvxgrp.org/cvxportfolio
  6. Solver: https://osqp.org/docs/

Data¶

  1. Index constituent weights
  2. Index constituent returns
  3. Index returns (just to plot benchmark)

Risk¶

Define Markowitz optimization risk term: past 5-year daily return to calculate covariance matrix $${\sigma_{i,j}=\operatorname {cov} [r_{i},r_{j}]=\operatorname {E} [(r_{i}-\operatorname {E} [r_{i}])(r_{j}-\operatorname {E} [r_{j}])]}$$

Optimizer¶

$$\max \left( {{\sum_i{w_i * r_i}-\gamma \sum_{i,j}{w_i * w_j * \sigma_{i,j}}}} \right)$$

subject to:
Each components weight should deviate from CSI300 weight less than 3%. $$ \left| \frac{w_i}{w_i^{csi}} - 1 \right| < 3\% $$ Turnover rate should be less than 15%. $$ \sum{\left| \Delta w_i \right|} < 15\% $$

In [7]:
# build optimizer policy
ir_policy = IndexRebalOpt(alpha, [gamma_risk * risk_model], idx_weight, 
                          tracking_error=0.03, turnover_limit=0.15)
